

---
const pageTitle = "Conscious and Unconscious";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
      }

      p { margin-bottom: 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: var(--soft);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        [ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]
        [ <a class="blue" href="/foundations">foundations index</a> ]
        [ <a class="green" href="/foundations/persona">previous</a> ]
        [ <a class="red" href="/foundations/individuation">next</a> ]
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <h1>Conscious and Unconscious</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">foundations / psyche / archive entry 003</p>

        <div class="divider">***</div>

        <p>
          Your mind is not only what you are aware of.
        </p>

        <p>
          What you call “you” is only a small surface layer. Beneath it exists a much larger field of thoughts, images, instincts, and patterns that operate without your awareness.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
          The conscious mind is the light. The unconscious is the depth it cannot fully see.
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title">the conscious</h2>

        <p>
          The conscious is what you know. It includes your current thoughts, decisions, and perceptions.
        </p>

        <p>
          It is focused, narrow, and limited. It helps you navigate the world, but it cannot contain the whole of your psyche.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">the unconscious</h2>

        <p>
          The unconscious contains everything outside of awareness. Forgotten memories, repressed emotions, instincts, dreams, and deeper patterns all live here.
        </p>

        <p>
          It is not empty. It is active.
        </p>

        <p>
          It expresses itself through dreams, impulses, attraction, fear, and sudden ideas.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
          What you do not face within yourself will appear to you as fate.
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title">the tension</h2>

        <p>
          The conscious and unconscious are not separate systems. They are in constant relationship.
        </p>

        <p>
          When the conscious mind becomes too one-sided, the unconscious compensates. This can appear as anxiety, confusion, or emotional disturbance.
        </p>

        <p>
          These are not random. They are signals.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">making the unconscious conscious</h2>

        <p>
          Growth happens when what is hidden becomes known.
        </p>

        <p>
          This does not mean controlling the unconscious. It means relating to it.
        </p>

        <p>
          Practices like <a class="blue" href="/dreams/active-imagination">active imagination</a>, dream work, and reflection allow this process to unfold.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is the foundation of <a class="green" href="/foundations/individuation">individuation</a>.
        </p>

        <div class="mini-links">
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations">back to foundations index</a>
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations/individuation">continue to: individuation</a>
          <a class="red" href="/dreams/active-imagination">imagination</a>
          <a class="green" href="/self/creativity-and-fantasy">creativity</a>
        </div>

        <p class="footer-note">what is unseen still shapes everything.</p>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>